Review: Almost half a century after the signing of the Helsinki Final Act in 1975, Michael Morgan’s book on this major event in the middle of the Cold War in Europe may be seen as a courageous effort to provide an in-depth historical analysis of this highly remarkable process which paved the way for major changes in the post-World War II order in Europe.
